venue.name: Xin Mei Le Bak Kut Teh

tips.text: This bakuteh version contains  當归 herb which I like. But pepper fans beware that there is almost no pepper taste in the soup. 煮炒is good. Try their prawn paste chicken. #ThomtoriEats #bakuteh
Good healthy food for good price. Love the hummus with falafel.
Their food are very satisfying!! Definitely will go back again.
Food is totally overpriced but drinks and atmosphere at bar upstairs are great, so have dinner somewhere else and come here only for drinks.

formattedAddress: Blk 7 Tanjong Pagar Plaza, #01-103 165 Tanjong Pagar Road
location.address: Blk 7 Tanjong Pagar Plaza, #01-103 165 Tanjong Pagar Road

tips.text: Great chill out place for neighborhood area !
Reasonable price with good food. Nice to enjoy the mood of korea
Friendly & excellent service, especially for young kids. Food is ok although dessert choices not inspiring. Coffee's not bad.
Try the steaks on the menu, they are famous for that.
You will see the whole family. Spot their son and daughter: The T-ara and SHINee lookalikes.
깐풍기가 정말 맛있네요. 짜장면은 괜찮았어요. 다음엔 탕수육도 먹어봐야겠어요.
Wonderful, comfort food. Really like the bakwan kepeting and the ayam buah keluak.
Love the Vintage decor. Try the Ungai Benedict for Brunch.
Amazing, one of the best restaurants I've been to in Singapore or elsewhere...

venue.name: Amoy St Boon Kee Prawn Noodle

tips.text: The best best best best Prawn noodles, ever! The dry noodle is a must-try, all the people working around there know of this underrated stall!
The ambience is really cozy, a great place for gatherings. Best food of the night — Carne de Porco à Alentejana. It's not on the menu though.

formattedAddress: The Westin Singapore (Asia Square Tower 2, 12 Marina View)

tips.text: Great place to chill. Price are very reasonable!
What a great find. Feels like in Australia. Wholesome food with an easy vibe. For something light, don't miss the quinoa salad or the granola yogurt. For something heavier, try the smoked mackerel!
Oysters are $2-3 apiece during happy hour – 5pm to 7pm every day, and all night on Mondays!
The best eggs ever!

location.address: #01-58, Amoy Street Food Centre, 7 Maxwell Road

tips.text: the food here packs a punch! spicy shiok
One of the best places for chicken wings in Singapore!
Beef rague papadelle aka beef pasta
Good quality food well priced business lunch set menu. Angus beef onglet and chips cooked perfectly, and loved the Apple crumble dessert.
Have you tried their coffee and toasties? Well, you should.
Fried chicken. That is all.
It's not pancetta but who gives a fork when it's so baconlicious. Honestly I could have one more plate of this al dente masterpiece. Nevermind that it's a work-weekday.

My best, love their earl grey lavender & rose raspberry pistachio cakes, & their wonderful matcha green teas. A wifi'd café downstairs, & a flower shoppe upstairs. Super bouquets blooms 4 all seasons.
Everything is wonderful. A real beef experience.
The Awesome Salad is truly awesome: a generous serving of smoked salmon, duck rillettes, salami, chicken breast and avocado on a bed of greens, with a side of pesto panini
Try the Burgers!! A MUST 😍
Best korean restaurant that I've been to along Amoy street. Weekday set lunches are $12 and delicious!!! Also, free seaweed 😆
Wong Ah Yoke (food critic) likes: Breaded Kaffir Lime Fresh Oysters, Roasted US Bay Scallop, Grain-fed US Holstein Ribeye 365 Days, Spiced Deboned Red Snapper. Source: Sunday Times

tips.text: Char siew here is grrreat!!! Thick juicy slices unlike the paper-thin, dry ones you get everywhere else in Singapore!
Thursday special! Corona for $2.50!

contact.facebookName: 왕대박 Wang Dae Bak Korean BBQ

tips.text: Good food with excellent service! must try the pork rib stew during lunch! not a common korean dish found in SG
Best Italian food in Singapore!
Chicken chop and fish and chips are delish! ;-)

venue.name: Ginza Tendon Itsuki by Ramen Keisuke

tips.text: Humongous portions of tendon for special set (chicken, prawn, etc). Highlight def is fried onsen egg. Break the yolk over rice for instant heaven! The washroom has heated toilet seat cover & bidet.
Good creative food using modern cooking techniques. The $58 set is a bargain!

formattedAddress: 5 Banda St, #01-52 K88 Coffee House (Sago Lane)

tips.text: Best sausage! Try Smoked Pork with Cheese!
Try the wagyu burrata, squid ink risotto and finish it off with the chocolate fondant - perfect!

formattedAddress: Food Garden, Asia Square (12 Marina View)

tips.text: Love their create your own meal and $9.90 is pretty good for CBD pricing. Chicken is tender and flavourful! Eating healthy ain't so tough afterall!

venue.name: Imperial Treasure Super Peking Duck Restaurant 御寶至尊烤鴨店

tips.text: Duck of course. Not as crowded as the Paragon branch.
The dinosaur bone is crazy epic.

venue.name: Shun Ka Shuu Tou (春夏秋冬)

tips.text: Unfortunately this time the lunch was rather disappointing 😩 sushi n sashimi wasn't that super fresh 😁 overall the service was good 😊
Drinks time every Friday and Saturday night 10.30pm - 1am!
Flat white was really good. Recommended for coffee addicts.
Wagyu beef and set meals! Sashimis are so fresh! Authentic Japanese! very friendly staff too! This is now officially one of my fave in Tras area.
Seating for abt 30 ppl. But can appear limited during lunch time ;-)
